every call is content addressed by cached(kind, key, fn), which hashes the kind of call, the model id, only the lang/ folder that kind reads and that kind's own system prompt together with the key, returns the json under that hash in CACHE if it is there and otherwise runs fn once and writes it, so an untouched program recompiles byte for byte, an edit to the codegen sheet does not invalidate lowering, and the second identical call costs nothing;